title: After Gophers Sweep, UMD Retains Focus
text:
After Gophers Sweep, UMD Retains Focus 
By Zach Schneider   10:49 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- The University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) men's hockey team has won a school record six straight games against intrastate rival Minnesota, but players and coaches say the team's focus has already shifted to the future. 
The Bulldogs swept a home-and-home series this past weekend against the Gophers, leaving the team open to a possible hangover this weekend against Notre Dame. 
Click here to subscribe to our daily newsletter. 
Some of the veterans, though, say that's not an issue. 
"Evert game in college hockey is big, whether it's conference or non-conference," sophomore Jared Thomas said. "Whatever it is, every game is important in its own way." 
"With Minnesota, there's always that extra jump you have in your step," junior Kyle Osterberg admitted. "But now that we know what we have as a team, it won't be hard to get ready and prepare for games." 
UMD's road series against Notre Dame will be aired this weekend on the My 9 Sports Network, with Friday scheduled for a 5:05 p.m. start and Saturday's for 5:35 p.m.
